        solver          PBiCGStab;
        preconditioner  diagonal;
        tolerance       1e-06;
        relTol          0.01;
    }
}
```

This follows the same pattern as the `p` solver (since `k` is also a scalar field solved via a Laplacian-like discretization) and ensures the k-epsilon model can properly solve for the turbulent kinetic energy during the PIMPLE iteration. The `k` field equation is symmetric (diffusion-dominated), so `PCG` with `DIC` is appropriate.

